      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
        <lg met="āryā" n="1">
          <l n="ab" real="+++++--+++++-+-+---"><lb n="1"/>ye dhammā hetu-prabhavā <space/> tesaṁ hetuṁ tathāgato Avaca</l>
          <l n="cd"><lb n="2"/>tesañ ca yo nirodho <space/> Evaṁ-vādī mahā-samano</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
      <div source="bib:Skilling2019_01" type="translation">
        <p n="1" rend="stanza">The states arisen from a cause / Their cause the Tathāgata proclaims, / As well as their cessation: This is the teaching of the Great Ascetic.</p>
      </div>
      <div source="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01" type="translation" xml:lang="fra">
        <p>Les conditions qui proviennent d'une cause, d'elles le Tathāgata a dit la cause, d'elles aussi ce qui est la suppression. Telle est la doctrine du Grand Ascète.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="commentary">
        <p>The French translation is c.</p>
      </div>
